4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under existing law, the Industrial Development
6 and Training Institute operates as a Division of the
7 Department of Commerce to provide workforce development
8 for businesses and education and training to the
9 state's workforce. If AIDT plans to construct a new
10 building or renovate an existing building, the AIDT
11 director must certify to the Governor that the proposal
12 is consistent with the Strategic Workforce Plan.
13 This bill would revise references to the plan to
14 the new comprehensive statewide economic development
15 strategic plan.
16 Consistent with Executive Order 2012-31 and Act
17 2013-118, AIDT's contracts are generally exempt from
18 review by the Legislative Contract Review Oversight
19 Committee, with an exception for legal service
20 contracts.
21 This bill would codify the existing AIDT
22 exemption from the general contract review requirements
23 of the Legislative Contract Review Oversight Committee,
24 and would also exempt its legal services contracts from
25 review by the committee.
26 Also under existing law, every governmental
27 body, unless exempted, is subject to the requirements
28 of the state procurement laws when making procurements
Page 1

of the state procurement laws when making procurements
SB325 INTRODUCED
29 for goods and services other than public works.
30 This bill would provide that AIDT is exempt from
31 the requirements of the state procurement law for the
32 procurement of supplies and services other than public
33 works.
