36 A BILL
37 TO BE ENTITLED
38 AN ACT
39
40 Relating to the Department of Commerce; to amend
41 Section 41-29-282, Code of Alabama 1975, to provide that the
42 Alabama Industrial Development Training Institute (AIDT)
43 within the Department of Commerce is exempt from the state
44 procurement law and review by the Contract Review Permanent
45 Legislative Oversight Committee; and to further provide for
46 the strategic plan applicable to AIDT.
47 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
48 Section 1. Section 41-29-282, Code of Alabama 1975, is
49 amended to read as follows:
50 "§41-29-282
51 (a) AIDT shall operate as a division of the Department
52 of Commerce. All of the powers, authority, duties, functions,
53 policies, and funds of, and appropriations to AIDT previously
54 conferred upon or granted to AIDT reporting to the State Board
55 of Education through the Division of Vocational-Technical
56 Education or by Alabama Executive Order No. 2012-31 are
Page 2

Education or by Alabama Executive Order No. 2012-31 are
