57 confirmed, ratified, continued, transferred to, and vested in
58 AIDT.
59 (b) All contracts, leases, grants, and agreements
60 previously entered by AIDT shall continue in full force and
61 effect without modification or interruption by this
62 restructuring. AIDT may enter into new contracts, agreements,
63 and other instruments necessary to procure goods, services,
64 training, and related resources in furtherance of its purpose,
65 as set forth in Section 41-29-280, and shall be exempt from
66 both of the following:
67 (1) Article 5 of Chapter 4 of Title 41, relating to the
68 state procurement law.
69 (2) Chapter 2 of Title 29, relating to the Permanent
70 Legislative Committees, including the Contract Review
71 Legislative Oversight Committee.
72 (c) All property currently owned by AIDT shall continue
73 to be the property of AIDT. If AIDT plans to construct any new
74 building, retrofit or renovate any of its existing buildings,
75 or request or receive any state or federal funding to
76 construct, retrofit, or renovate any of its buildings, the
77 AIDT director shall first certify to a the Governor that the
78 proposal is consistent with the Strategic Workforce Plan
79 comprehensive statewide economic development strategic plan.
80 (d) AIDT shall continue to be headed by a director, who
81 shall be appointed by the Secretary of Commerce and shall
82 serve at his or her pleasure. The powers, duties, and
83 qualifications required of the director shall be as set forth
84 in the AIDT Policy Manual, as amended from time to time and
